ngton, the 1st president of the US; or adoption of the surname in 1 above, in most cases probably for the same reason.","History: George Washington (1732–99), 1st president of the US (1789–97), was born at Bridges Creek, VA. His great-grandfather had emigrated from Dillicar in Westmorland in 1658. George Washington was a slaveowner, but he became troubled with the institution of slavery. Shortly before his death he decided that his slaves have to be freed after the death of his wife. — With the passage of time, the surname Washington has come to be borne by more African Americans (around 90% of all bearers) than English-Americans. A prominent example was the educator Booker T. Washington (1856–1915), born a slave in VA, who adopted his surname from his stepfather, Washington Ferguson."],"variants":[{"name":"President","meanings":["African American: from the English vocabulary word <i>president</i>, probably adopted as a surname in honor of one of the early presidents of the US (compare   Washington   and   Jefferson  ) or simply because of the importance of the presidential function."]},{"name":"Washinton","meanings":["Altered form of English   Washington  ."]}]},{"name":"Walter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French personal name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i>, <i>hari</i> ‘army’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, superseding the native Old English form, <i>Wealdhere</i>. It was a very popular name in medieval England, normally pronounced ‘Water’."],"variants":[{"name":"Walther","meanings":["from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i> ‘army’; name of the famous medieval minnesinger  Walther von der Vogelweide  (  <i>c.</i>1170– <i>c.</i>1230 )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Walter de Washington was born about 1270, his father, John de Washington, was 52 and his mother, F de Washington, was 21. He had at least 1 daughter with Alicia. He died in Durham, Durham, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Abt 1270–":"umbes 1270–Surnud","1270–Male":"1270–Surnud","1283–Female":"1283–Surnud","1290–Female":"1290–Surnud","1323–Female":"1323–Surnud","1220–Male":"1220–Surnud","1250–Female":"1250–Surnud","1323":"1323","1220":"1220","Abt 1323":"umbes 1323","1250":"1250","1283":"1283","Abt 1270":"umbes 1270","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","Durham, Durham unitary authority, Durham, England, United Kingdom":"Durham, Durham, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1270–":"noin 1270–Kuollut","1270–Male":"1270–Kuollut","1283–Female":"1283–Kuollut","1290–Female":"1290–Kuollut","1323–Female":"1323–Kuollut","1220–Male":"1220–Kuollut","1250–Female":"1250–Kuollut","1323":"1323","1220":"1220","Abt 1323":"noin 1323","1250":"1250","1283":"1283","Abt 1270":"noin 1270","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","Durham, Durham unitary authority, Durham, England, United Kingdom":"Durham, Durham, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1270–":"environ 1270–Décédé","1270–Male":"1270–Décédé","1283–Female":"1283–Décédée","1290–Female":"1290–Décédée","1323–Female":"1323–Décédée","1220–Male":"1220–Décédé","1250–Female":"1250–Décédée","1323":"1323","1220":"1220","Abt 1323":"environ 1323","1250":"1250","1283":"1283","Abt 1270":"environ 1270","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","Durham, Durham unitary authority, Durham, England, United Kingdom":"Durham, Durham, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Walter de Washington est né environ 1270, son père, John de Washington, avait 52 ans et sa mère, F de Washington, avait 21 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Alicia. Il est décédé à Durham, Durham, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni."},"de":{"Abt 1270–":"um 1270–Verstorben","1270–Male":"1270–Verstorben","1283–Female":"1283–Verstorben","1290–Female":"1290–Verstorben","1323–Female":"1323–Verstorben","1220–Male":"1220–Verstorben","1250–Female":"1250–Verstorben","1323":"1323","1220":"1220","Abt 1323":"um 1323","1250":"1250","1283":"1